Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle at neck join. Clay fine pink-brown. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Antimachos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0383.09.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0809)
